<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>West Brom are looking to complete the signing of Wigan Athletic centre-back Cedric Kipre this week in a £900,000 deal. </p>

<p>The 23-year-old also had an offer from Blackburn. </p>

<p>Albion will discuss whether to pursue loan moves for Watford's Troy Deeney and Brighton's Shane Duffy this week. West Ham and Celtic are also interested in Duffy. </p>

<p>West Brom are looking to complete signing of Wigan's Cedric Kipre in £900,000 deal</p>

<p>Kipre, formerly of Leicester City, was impressive last season and has attracted interest from a number of clubs. </p>

<p>Crisis club Wigan sold Jamal Lowe to Swansea City on Thursday and have interest from Sheffield Wednesday in Josh Windass.</p>

<p>Wigan's administrators, Begbies-Traynor say there are four bidders at an advanced stage pushing to buy the club and its assets for around £4million. Two are UK-based and two are from USA. </p>

<p>The 23-year-old has also had an offer from Blackburn as Albion also pursue Troy Deeney </p>
